1510
01:29:45.988 --> 01:29:49.928
that integrates via homology directed repair into the endogenous trac

1511
01:29:49.948 --> 01:29:53.748
locus of primary human T cells. And so the idea

1512
01:29:53.848 --> 01:29:57.688
is that after a few rounds of simple digestions and ligations, you're

1513
01:29:57.768 --> 01:30:01.728
able to generate a single HDRT or homology-directed

1514
01:30:01.768 --> 01:30:04.928
repair template that contains multiple perturbations.

1515
01:30:05.448 --> 01:30:09.258
And the ease of this process allows it to be scaled rapidly, making

1516
01:30:09.308 --> 01:30:12.968
combinatorial pooled knockin screenings easier than ever before.

1517
01:30:14.048 --> 01:30:17.288
And so I guess just to go back to my initial slide, we've

1518
01:30:17.348 --> 01:30:21.268
identified genetic signatures in responders versus non-responder

1519
01:30:21.308 --> 01:30:25.128
infusion products from patients, and CRISPR-all allows us to take those

1520
01:30:25.168 --> 01:30:29.088
